TY  - JOUR
TI  - ECONOMIC PREDICTIONS WITH BIG DATA
AU  - Giannone, Domenico
AU  - Lenza, Michele
AU  - Primiceri, Giorgio E.
AB  - [We compare sparse and dense representations of predictive models in macroeconomics, microeconomics, and finance. To deal with a large number of possible predictors, we specify a prior that allows for both variable selection and shrinkage. The posterior distribution does not typically concentrate on a single sparse model, but on a wide set of models that often include many predictors.]
